snippet.textDisplay:
Off Topic Question:

Am I the only one That feels like his family can‘t Cook for shit? You always hear of how it „tastes like grandma‘s „instert dish““ or „just like mom used to make it“. For me, when i hear these things, it means Death on a Plate is heading towards me.
I spend 1-3 hours cooking everyday, if i‘ve got the Time for it which is mostly the case.
I am not a pro, But i know the Basics and i‘d say i‘m definetly above average.
But the shit that My Family does...boiling noodles for 1hour+, burnt meat thats raw on the inside (Not a little, FUCKING RAW), for god‘s sake my aunt once used cheese instead of oil to cook a piece of meat because she thought the cheese had enough fat in it. And everytime i suggest to do something different they get pissed.
Am I the only one who‘s Family can‘t cook anything?

Note: I‘m Not a native speaker if there‘s any Problem

snippet.textDisplay:
As someone who lived in Chicago, and went to Mexican restaurants where they barely spoke English, I can tell you that part of what makes a good steak taco, or carne asada, is that they really finely slice and chop up the beef, into little tiny strips, and what makes an amazing as when they grill it, and it comes off the grill and has that little bit of crunch to it.
When people who don't get traditional Mexican food that often, make tacos and burritos they absolutely ruin it with big sloppy slabs of meat.

I've been adding all that gross marinated cabbage to it? I don't want a bunch of crappy sauce in my taco.

Onions, lettuce, cilantro and a little bit of lime... Nice hot salsa...

This over conflated nonsense is not a taco and definitely not Mexican Street food..

snippet.textDisplay: street tacos are simple, this douche needs a set of cutlery to make toast.  I can cook all that stuff with one skillet and a knife.  Done.  If you want real tacos, you have to get dried beans and soak them overnight, and add seasoning, and use real Mexican cheeses.  Otherwise everything's simple, just like taco bell.  The only other magic trick is putting green chilies in the rice.  Mexican sauce is called mole.  Pronounced like guacamole.  Prepping the meats by marinating them in traditional mole is the only other thing you need to know about street tacos.
